--> OS module provides the functions that can intaract with the operating system.

--> To get all operations about the OS module we need to give the command of print(dir(os))

--> To get the current working directory we need to use the os.getcwd()

--> To change the directory we will use the os.chdir("path")

--> to create the directory we will use the os.mkdir()

--> to create the sub directory we will use the os.makedirs("directory/sub-directory")

--> to remove the file we will use the os.rmdir()

--> to remove the directory inside the directory we will use the os.removedirs()

--> to rename the file we will use the command of os.rename("original","modified")






